  "description": [
    "The Manifest Destiny of Florida son when the demand is at its height as this state of Florida It is bound to be for nil time to come the great garden spot of the nation That is its manifest destiny But that does not preclude a glow of pride in the big things that are go ing on to the south of us on the idle acres down there The big ranches will have their day and contribute much to the wealth of the state and nation They are doing the prelimi nary work for the man with the hoe and when he begin3 to crowd for a place in the Florida sunshine they will give place to him as they have done elsewhere and Florida will go FUNDAMENTAL FACTS Tampa Times As we read of the great cattle ranches being organized in the south ern rart of the state we cannot help a feeling of pride and satisfaction Great areas are being fenced and stocked with cattle In some in stances the acres put under fence amount to as many as a quarter of a million There are several equaling or approaching this size and numbers of smaller ones"
